HEADWORD: Classification
<hw>Clas`si*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>classification</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of forming into a class
or classes; a distribution into groups, as classes, orders, families,
etc., according to some common relations or affinities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Artificial classification</b></col>. <fld>(Science)</fld>
<cd>See under <er>Artifitial</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Classificatory</ent>⟦br⟧
